  {
    "term": "effective resistance",
    "source_id": "theory-calculation-alternating-current-phenomena",
    "modern_equivalent": "AC resistance or equivalent resistance representing total real-power loss",
    "occurrence_count_in_ocr": 33,
    "steinmetz_usage": "Distinguished from true ohmic resistance; it represents total power expenditure, including loss mechanisms outside the conductor.",
    "mathematical_meaning": "For sinusoidal AC, effective resistance is the real-power coefficient in P = I^2 r.",
    "conceptual_meaning": "This term lets hysteresis, dielectric loss, eddy currents, leakage, and nonuniform current distribution appear as real-power effects without pretending they are simple DC resistance.",
